item.title: Men’s hockey 2s let two goals past them against UCL
item.author: Adam Miszewski,
item.description: On a rainy Sunday afternoon, the Imperial College Hockey Club Men’s 2nd XI wearily approached the UCL hockey ground late after a tiring morning of push starting a seriously defective Union minibus. However, the team got fired up soon enough and went onto the pitch with the desire to win which led to …
